<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-08T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-08T14:00:00-05:00" n="139" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d139">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112A/1823a</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MRS1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-08T15:00:00-04:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">May 8, 1918, 3 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Government considering possibility of establishment of white list for
                                China and has cabled instructions for consuls to report on names
                                appearing on British list and such eliminations from and additions
                                thereto as they have to suggest. Whole question of cooperation in
                                war trade policies under discussion here with Japanese
                                Ambassador.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>